    }

    #[test]
    fn default_to_baz() {
        assert(foo_if_fizz('literally anything') == 'baz', 'anything else returns baz');
    }
}
```

The `#[cfg(test)]` attribute enables conditional compilation, meaning the `mod tests` block will only be compiled when running tests. `felt252` is the basic field element type in Cairo, commonly used for string literals and general-purpose integers.

